empty-cert-action.name: empty-cert-action
empty-cert-action.help: Action of an empty client certificate.

options.name: accept
options.help: Accept the SSL handshake if the client certificate is empty.

options.name: block
options.help: Block the SSL handshake if the client certificate is empty.

ldb-method.name: ldb-method
ldb-method.help: Method used to distribute sessions to real servers.

options.name: static
options.help: Distribute to server based on source IP.

options.name: round-robin
options.help: Distribute to server based round robin order.

options.name: weighted
options.help: Distribute to server based on weight.

options.name: least-session
options.help: Distribute to server with lowest session count.

options.name: least-rtt
options.help: Distribute to server with lowest Round-Trip-Time.

options.name: first-alive
options.help: Distribute to the first server that is alive.

options.name: http-host
options.help: Distribute to server based on host field in HTTP header.

options.name: sub-string
options.help: Match the pattern if a string contains the sub-string.

options.name: regex
options.help: Match the pattern with a regular expression.

realservers.name: realservers
realservers.help: Select the real servers that this Access Proxy will distribute traffic to.

address.name: address
address.help: Address or address group of the real server.

ip.name: ip
ip.help: IP address of the real server.

port.name: port
port.help: Port for communicating with the real server.

mappedport.name: mappedport
mappedport.help: Port for communicating with the real server.

status.name: status
status.help: Set the status of the real server to active so that it can accept traffic, or on standby or disabled so no traffic is sent.

weight.name: weight
weight.help: Weight of the real server. If weighted load balancing is enabled, the server with the highest weight gets more connections.

http-host.name: http-host
http-host.help: HTTP server domain name in HTTP header.

health-check.name: health-check
health-check.help: Enable to check the responsiveness of the real server before forwarding traffic.

health-check-proto.name: health-check-proto
health-check-proto.help: Protocol of the health check monitor to use when polling to determine server's connectivity status.

options.name: ping
options.help: Use PING to test the link with the server.

options.name: http
options.help: Use HTTP-GET to test the link with the server.

options.name: tcp-connect
options.help: Use a full TCP connection to test the link with the server.

persistence.name: persistence
persistence.help: Configure how to make sure that clients connect to the same server every time they make a request that is part of the same session.

http-cookie-domain-from-host.name: http-cookie-domain-from-host
http-cookie-domain-from-host.help: Enable/disable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP.

options.name: disable
options.help: Disable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP (use http-cooke-domain setting).

options.name: enable
options.help: Enable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP.

http-cookie-domain.name: http-cookie-domain
http-cookie-domain.help: Domain that HTTP cookie persistence should apply to.

http-cookie-path.name: http-cookie-path
http-cookie-path.help: Limit HTTP cookie persistence to the specified path.

http-cookie-generation.name: http-cookie-generation
http-cookie-generation.help: Generation of HTTP cookie to be accepted. Changing invalidates all existing cookies.

http-cookie-age.name: http-cookie-age
http-cookie-age.help: Time in minutes that client web browsers should keep a cookie. Default is 60 minutes. 0 = no time limit.

http-cookie-share.name: http-cookie-share
http-cookie-share.help: Control sharing of cookies across API Gateway. same-ip means a cookie from one virtual server can be used by another. Disable stops cookie sharing.

options.name: disable
options.help: Only allow HTTP cookie to match this API Gateway.

options.name: same-ip
options.help: Allow HTTP cookie to match any API Gateway with same IP.

https-cookie-secure.name: https-cookie-secure
https-cookie-secure.help: Enable/disable verification that inserted HTTPS cookies are secure.

options.name: disable
options.help: Do not mark cookie as secure, allow sharing between an HTTP and HTTPS connection.

options.name: enable
options.help: Mark inserted cookie as secure, cookie can only be used for HTTPS a connection.

saml-server.name: saml-server
saml-server.help: SAML service provider configuration for VIP authentication.

ssl-dh-bits.name: ssl-dh-bits
ssl-dh-bits.help: Number of bits to use in the Diffie-Hellman exchange for RSA encryption of SSL sessions.

ssl-algorithm.name: ssl-algorithm
ssl-algorithm.help: Permitted encryption algorithms for the server side of SSL full mode sessions according to encryption strength.

options.name: high
options.help: High encryption. Allow only AES and ChaCha.

options.name: medium
options.help: Medium encryption. Allow AES, ChaCha, 3DES, and RC4.

options.name: low
options.help: Low encryption. Allow AES, ChaCha, 3DES, RC4, and DES.

options.name: custom
options.help: Custom encryption. Use ssl-cipher-suites to select the cipher suites that are allowed.

ssl-cipher-suites.name: ssl-cipher-suites
ssl-cipher-suites.help: SSL/TLS cipher suites to offer to a server, ordered by priority.

versions.name: versions
versions.help: SSL/TLS versions that the cipher suite can be used with.

ssl-min-version.name: ssl-min-version
ssl-min-version.help: Lowest SSL/TLS version acceptable from a server.

ssl-max-version.name: ssl-max-version
ssl-max-version.help: Highest SSL/TLS version acceptable from a server.

server-pubkey-auth.name: server-pubkey-auth
server-pubkey-auth.help: Enable/disable SSH real server public key authentication.

options.name: disable
options.help: Disable SSH real server public key authentication.

options.name: enable
options.help: Enable SSH real server public key authentication with SSH certificate.

server-pubkey-auth-settings.name: server-pubkey-auth-settings
server-pubkey-auth-settings.help: Server SSH public key authentication settings.

source-address.name: source-address
source-address.help: Enable/disable appending source-address certificate critical option. This option ensure certificate only accepted from FortiGate source address.

cert-extension.name: cert-extension
cert-extension.help: Configure certificate extension for user certificate.

options.name: no
options.help: Certificate extension, server ignores the unsupported certificate extension.

options.name: yes
options.help: Critical option, server refuses to authorize if it cannnot recognise the critical option.

options.name: user
options.help: Certificate extension entry filled with authenticated username.

auth-ca.name: auth-ca
auth-ca.help: Name of the SSH server public key authentication CA.

ldb-method.help: Method used to distribute sessions to SSL real servers.

options.name: static

options.name: round-robin

options.name: weighted
options.help: Distribute to server based on weight.

options.name: least-session
options.help: Distribute to server with lowest session count.

options.name: least-rtt
options.help: Distribute to server with lowest Round-Trip-Time.

options.name: first-alive
options.help: Distribute to the first server that is alive.

realservers.name: realservers
realservers.help: Select the SSL real servers that this Access Proxy will distribute traffic to.
